subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Body with 21 leg-bearing segments. Spiracles oval-shaped (
Fig.17C
). Antennae with 19–21 antennomeres including first two and 1/3 of the third glabrous (
Fig. 16
). Coxosternal plate with 6(7)+6(7) teeth (
Fig. 16D
). Paramedian grooves distinct on tergites 3–20, but absent on sternites (
Fig. 17A
). Coxopleural process long, conical, with 3 apical spines (
Fig. 12A
). Spines on prefemur of the ultimate legs large and arranged in rows (
Figs 17D
, 
18B
).

